# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# COMMITTED DEPLOY CONFIG — pulled live on every box (VPS + vast.ai) via git.
# Sourced by serve.sh / boot.sh before the backend starts. VITE_* values are also
# read automatically by the Vite build.
#
#  NO SECRETS IN THIS FILE. It is committed to the git repo, so anything here is
#  visible to anyone with repo access. `dev-key` is the default OPEN dev key, not a
#  secret. If you ever need a real API key (e.g. KIMI_API_KEY), export it as a shell
#  env var on the box BEFORE running serve.sh — do NOT put it here.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Ports (VPS front door: http://76.13.176.135:5173 UI · :8001 API) ─────────
API_PORT=8001
UI_PORT=5173
VITE_API_PORT=8001
VITE_API_KEY=dev-key
VITE_REQUIRE_AUTH=false

# ── GPU LLM on vast.ai (211.72.13.201) ───────────────────────────────────────
# vast.ai maps the container's :11434 to a DIFFERENT external port that changes
# whenever the instance is recreated. Two steps to connect:
#   1) On the GPU box, bind Ollama to all interfaces (not just localhost):
#        OLLAMA_HOST=0.0.0.0:11434 ollama serve &
#        ollama pull llama3.1:8b
#   2) Get the external port mapped to 11434, then set OLLAMA_HOST below:
#        echo "$VAST_TCP_PORT_11434"      # vast.ai sets this on the box
#   …or skip editing this file and just use the Setup page → "Connect GPU" (it
#    persists to llm_connect.json, which is also committed, so the URL syncs too).
# Uncomment + set the real external port, then `git commit && git push`:
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://211.72.13.201:<external-port-for-11434>
OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.1:8b

# ── Autonomous engines (GPU autopilot, autobuild, recon allowlist) ───────────
LLM_AUTOPILOT_ENABLE=1
LLM_AUTOPILOT_CONCURRENCY=3
AUTOBUILD_BATCHES=2
AUTOBUILD_OCR=5
# Recon tools (katana/nuclei/etc.) only run against hosts you list here (your own /
# authorised assets). Empty/default = recon off against third parties.
RECON_ALLOWLIST=127.0.0.1,localhost
